comments: I did not make any notes. I thought some blue objects had the suffix -cow, and some red ones the suffix -coe. The objects had prefixes according to their shapes. I wondered if I should use the colour suffix rule even where i did not think it was the right word to try and help my partner get the right colour object, where different colours of the same object had the same word, for example zettyc. I found the audio a bit off putting as the pronunciation was the same for different spellings, this probably made my performance worse
